The '''Inchagiri Sampradaya''', also known as '''Nimbargi Sampradaya''', is a lineage of [[Hindu]] [[Navnath]] c.q. [[Lingayat]] [[Guru|teachers]] from [[Maharashtra]] which was started by [[Bhausaheb Maharaj|Shri Bhausaheb Maharaj]].<ref group=web name="ShantiKuteer">[http://www.shantikuteer.org/page.php?pi=21 ShantiKuteer Ashram, ''Bhausaheb Maharaj'']</ref> It is inspired by [[Deshastha Brahmin]] [[Sant Mat]] teachers as [[Dnyaneshwar]], [[Eknath]] and [[Samarth Ramdas]]. The Inchagiri Sampradaya has become well-known throughout the western world due to the popularity of [[Nisargadatta Maharaj|Sri Nisargadatta Maharaj]].

