{{Expand Armenian|Ներսես Ե Աշտարակեցի|date=October 2012}} {{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}} {{Infobox Patriarch | honorific-prefix = His Holiness | name = Nerses V | patriarch_of = | honorific-suffix = Supreme Patriarch and [[Catholicos of All Armenians]] | image = Портрет Нерсеса Аштаракеци.А.Овнатанян.jpg | caption = Nerses V Ashtaraketsi, by H. Hovnatanian. | ordination = | consecration = | enthroned = 1843 | ended = 1857 | church = [[Armenian Apostolic Church]] | see = Mother See of Holy Etchmiadzin | predecessor = [[John VIII of Armenia|John VIII]] | successor = [[Matthew I of Armenia|Matthew I]] | other_post = | birth_name = Toros Harutyuni Shahazizyan (Թորոս Հարությունի Շահազիզյան) | birth_date = 1770 | birth_place = [[Ashtarak]] | death_date = February 13, 1857 (age 86) | death_place = [[Ejmiatsin]], Armenia | buried = Mother Cathedral of Holy Etchmiadzin | nationality = [[Armenians|Armenian]] | religion = | residence = | parents = | spouse = | children = | occupation = | profession = | alma_mater = | signature = }}
'''Nerses V''' ({{lang-hy|Ներսես Ե Աշտարակեցի}}, {{IPA-hy|nɛɾsɛs jɛ aʃtaɾakɛtsʰi}}) (1770 – February 13, 1857), served as the [[Catholicos]] of the [[Armenian Apostolic Church]] between 1843 and 1857. Previously, he served as the leader of Diocese of [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] from 1811 to 1830, the leader of the Diocese of [[Bessarabia]] and [[Nakhichevan-on-Don|Nor Nakhichevan]] from 1830 to 1843.
Nerses V is buried near [[Etchmiadzin Cathedral|Mother Cathedral of Holy Etchmiadzin]].
