{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Nicholas Southwood''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Analytic philosophy|Analytic]] | institutions = [[Australian National University]] |main_interests = [[political philosophy]], [[moral philosophy]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = |influences = |awards = [[ARC Future Fellow]], [[Fulbright Scholarship]], [[University Medal]] (ANU) |website = }}
'''Nicholas Southwood''' is an Australian philosopher and Associate Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[Australian National University]]. He is a co-editor of the ''[[Journal of Political Philosophy]]'' and Director of the [[Centre for Moral, Social and Political Theory]]. Southwood is known for his research on [[contractualism]]<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Barnes |first1=R. Eric |title=Contractualism and the Foundations of Morality |journal=[[Australasian Journal of Philosophy]] |date=December 2012 |volume=90 |issue=4 |pages=815–818 |doi=10.1080/00048402.2012.728613 |url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00048402.2012.728613?journalCode=rajp20 |accessdate=19 August 2018 |language=en |issn=0004-8402}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Vallier |first1=Kevin |title=Review of Contractualism and the Foundations of Morality |journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]] |date=14 October 2012 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/contractualism-and-the-foundations-of-morality/ |accessdate=19 August 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bocchiola |first1=Michele |title=Nicholas Southwood: Contractualism and the Foundations of Morality |journal=[[Ethical Theory and Moral Practice]] |date=11 January 2015 |volume=18 |issue=4 |pages=873–875 |doi=10.1007/s10677-015-9559-7 |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10677-015-9559-7 |accessdate=19 August 2018 |language=en |issn=1386-2820}}</ref> and [[social philosophy]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Theuns |first1=Tom |title=Book Review: Political Theory: Explaining NormsExplaining Norms by BrennanGeoffreyErikssonLinaGoodwinRobert E. and SouthwoodNicholas. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2013. 290 pp., £35.00, ISBN 9780199654680 |journal=[[Political Studies Review]] |date=12 January 2015 |volume=13 |issue=1 |pages=82–82 |doi=10.1111/1478-9302.12073_4 |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/1478-9302.12073_4 |accessdate=19 August 2018 |language=en |issn=1478-9299}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Spiekermann |first1=Kai |title=Explaining Norms, Geoffrey Brennan, Lina Eriksson, Robert E. Goodin and Nicholas Southwood. Oxford University Press, 2013, vii + 290 pages. |journal=[[Economics & Philosophy]] |date=March 2015 |volume=31 |issue=1 |pages=174–181 |doi=10.1017/S0266267114000467 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/economics-and-philosophy/article/explaining-norms-geoffrey-brennan-lina-eriksson-robert-e-goodin-and-nicholas-southwood-oxford-university-press-2013-vii-290-pages/FEE5F4B4D81E0CC53E816764AC57902C |accessdate=19 August 2018 |language=en |issn=0266-2671}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gaus |first1=Gerald |title=Review of Explaining Norms |journal=NDPR |date=4 February 2014 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/explaining-norms/ |accessdate=19 August 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref>
==Books== * ''Contractualism and the Foundations of Morality'', Oxford University Press, 2010, {{ISBN|9780199664658}} * ''Explaining Norms'', with [[Geoffrey Brennan]], [[Lina Eriksson]] and [[Robert E. Goodin]], Oxford University Press, 2013, {{ISBN|9780199654680}}
